First of all, a windows 32 bit process cannot use more that 3.2 gb of ram. 

A know leak are the thermal indicators. press F10 to disable them at every launch.

Are this all the mods you have? No mods with a lot of parts?

It might not be the indicators, thanks to tests run by AlmostDifferent it seems the issue of running out of memory when overheating is caused by the PPFX edge highlighting, disable it and you should see an improvement.

> 
> It might not be the indicators, thanks to tests run by AlmostDifferent it seems the issue of running out of memory when overheating is caused by the PPFX edge highlighting, disable it and you should see an improvement.

Jupp that was it. I Disabled the PPFX edhe highlighting. And no more Memory Problem. And i even think it looks better that way. The highlighting always anoyed me. 

So a win/win for me

Thanks alot both of you.
